CONVERSION OPTIMIZATION TACTICS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. DUAL CTA STRATEGY
   Every hero section offers two options:
   - Primary: "Get started now" (high intent)
   - Secondary: "Explore more" (low intent)
   Reduces decision paralysis while capturing both user types.

2. SOCIAL PROOF PROXIMITY
   Trust signals placed directly adjacent to CTAs.
   Rating appears immediately below action buttons.

3. PROBLEM-SOLUTION NARRATIVE (Features-2)
   "Before Prospect" → "After Prospect" storytelling.
   Addresses pain points before presenting features.

4. MULTIPLE CONVERSION MOMENTS
   CTAs appear every 2-3 sections throughout page.
   Never more than one scroll away from an action.

5. PRIVACY REASSURANCE
   "We never share your data with third parties"
   Appears near every form submission.

6. LOW-FRICTION ENTRY
   Free tier prominently displayed.
   "Start with Free" reduces commitment anxiety.

7. SPECIFICITY IN METRICS
   Not "faster" but "87% reduction"
   Not "better" but "3x improvement in forecast accuracy"

8. HUMAN PHOTOGRAPHY
   Real team photos over illustrations.
   Customer headshots over generic avatars.


CONTENT HIERARCHY
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                                                                             │
│   LEVEL 1: Main headline (largest, bold)                                    │
│            Communicates primary value proposition                           │
│                                                                             │
│   LEVEL 2: Section headlines                                                │
│            Introduces each major content block                              │
│                                                                             │
│   LEVEL 3: Subheadlines/descriptions                                        │
│            Supporting context and explanations                              │
│                                                                             │
│   LEVEL 4: Feature titles                                                   │
│            Individual capability names                                      │
│                                                                             │
│   LEVEL 5: Body text                                                        │
│            Detailed descriptions and explanations                           │
│                                                                             │
│   LEVEL 6: Captions/labels                                                  │
│            Metadata, dates, categories                                      │
│                                                                             │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘


