================================================================================
PAGE-BY-PAGE ANALYSIS
================================================================================

HOMEPAGES (/, /home-2, /home-3)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Purpose: A/B testing different value propositions and visual approaches

Home 1: Speed/efficiency angle ("Fast-Moving Businesses")
Home 2: AI/technology angle ("Robust AI for Finance Sector")
Home 3: Integration/unification angle ("Unite your Data, Tools, and Decisions")

Key Insight: Same product, three positioning strategies.


FEATURES PAGES (/features-1, /features-2, /features-3)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Features-1: Product capability catalog (tabbed interface)
Features-2: Problem-solution narrative (before/after storytelling)
Features-3: Integration directory (CMS-driven, filterable)

Key Insight: Different buyer personas need different feature presentations.


ABOUT PAGES (/about-1, /about-2, /about-3)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
About-1: Company story + leadership team
About-2: Culture + careers + recruitment
About-3: Technology + infrastructure credentials

Key Insight: "About" serves multiple audiences (customers, candidates, technical buyers).


PRICING (/pricing)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- 4 tiers: Free ($0), Basic ($19), Pro ($39), Enhanced ($79)
- No monthly/annual toggle
- No "recommended" tier highlighted
- Feature comparison in two categories per tier
- FAQ accordion below

Key Insight: Neutral presentation lets users self-select tier.


CUSTOMERS (/customers)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- 3 featured customer stories
- Card format with metric, quote, and CTA to full story
- Social proof header with rating

Key Insight: Metrics-first approach (lead with number, explain with quote).


CUSTOMER STORIES (/customers/continuum, /customers/intertial)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- Hero with company info + location + industry
- Single prominent metric
- Pull quotes throughout
- Related case study at bottom

Key Insight: Template for repeatable success story format.


BLOG (/blog, /blog-posts/*)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Listing:
- Vertical card stack (not grid)
- Date + category + headline + excerpt
- No author on cards
- No pagination visible

Article:
- Author with photo at top
- Centered readable column width
- Images with captions break up text
- Related posts at bottom
- No visible social sharing buttons

Key Insight: Content-first, minimal chrome.


CAREERS (/careers/senior-product-designer)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- Breadcrumb navigation back to careers
- Role + location + type header
- Responsibilities in bullet points
- "Why Prospect?" company pitch section
- Application form embedded (no separate ATS link)

Key Insight: Sells the company alongside the role.


INTEGRATIONS (/integrations/*, /integration-categories/*)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Detail Page:
- Integration name + logo + category tags
- "What this integration does" bullet list
- Related integrations grid below

Category Page:
- Filterable by category (Payments, Finance, Data, Collaboration)
- Card grid with logo, description, "See Integration" CTA

Key Insight: CMS-driven directory pattern.


UTILITY PAGES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Style Guide: Component showcase (not comprehensive design system)
404: Minimal, clear recovery path ("Back to Home")


================================================================================
BEST PRACTICES & PATTERNS WORTH BORROWING
================================================================================

WHAT PROSPECT DOES EXCEPTIONALLY WELL
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. MULTIPLE PAGE VARIATIONS
   Three versions of key pages (Home, Features, About) enable:
   - A/B testing different positioning
   - Different buyer persona journeys
   - Narrative flexibility without rebuilding

2. TRUST SIGNAL SATURATION
   Social proof appears every 2-3 sections:
   - Rating badges
   - Avatar stacks
   - Client logos
   - Named testimonials
   - Quantified results
   Never feels salesy because it's integrated naturally.

3. PROBLEM-SOLUTION NARRATIVE (Features-2)
   The "Before/After" pattern transforms feature lists into stories:
   - "Before Prospect: scattered communication, low morale"
   - "After Prospect: unified visibility, reclaimed evenings"
   Emotional resonance > feature enumeration.

4. METRICS-FIRST TESTIMONIALS
   Lead with the number, explain with the quote:
   "87% reduction in reporting time"
   → Then the human story behind it
   Specificity builds credibility.

5. DUAL CTA PATTERN
   Every conversion moment offers two paths:
   - High intent: "Get started now"
   - Low intent: "Explore more"
   Reduces bounce from decision paralysis.

6. HUMAN PHOTOGRAPHY
   Real faces throughout:
   - Team leadership with bios
   - Customer headshots with titles
   - Office location photography
   Builds trust through authenticity.

7. GENEROUS WHITESPACE
   Sections breathe. Content isn't cramped.
   Professional aesthetic over information density.

8. SCROLL ANIMATION RESTRAINT
   Subtle fade-in + translate on scroll.
   No aggressive motion that distracts.
   "Intentional motion" philosophy.


PATTERNS WORTH BORROWING FOR ADVYSER
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

